@Ycnt_ibdonlyjen @EmmersonKathryn @VicGovDHHS @BOM_au Great question Jen. N. hemisphere trees (eg birch) wind-pollinated and abundant in native forests. Smaller numbers of these non-native trees here means fewer (but not no) problems. Pasture grasses also wind-pollinated and abundant in W. Vic. Do count tree pollen but not daily.
RT @AsthmaAUS: For official daily pollen counts and forecasts you can follow @BrisbanePollen @CanberraPollen @MelbournePollen @SydneyPollen

@Ycnt_ibdonlyjen @EmmersonKathryn @VicGovDHHS @BOM_au Grass pollen is the major cause of seasonal hay fever and allergies but grasses only flower part of the year (the bit we count). Use our free app to tell us about your symptoms.
